# Project stack description — example

# Copy to .autopilot/stack.md and edit for your project.
# This file is loaded by scripts/codex-review.ts and included in Codex's
# system prompt so reviews are stack-aware.

A Next.js 15 App Router application with:
- TypeScript, React 19, Tailwind CSS
- PostgreSQL via Prisma
- Redis for rate limiting and session cache
- Vercel deployment
- Vitest for unit tests, Playwright for E2E
- OpenAI gpt-4o for LLM calls

Conventions:
- All DB mutations go through `lib/db/*.ts` services (never raw SQL in route handlers)
- API routes live under `app/api/` and return `NextResponse.json({ data })` on success or `{ error }` with status
- Feature flags via `lib/flags.ts` (env-driven, no external provider)

Things that should flag CRITICAL:
- Raw SQL without parameterization
- Missing rate limit on public POST endpoints
- Uncaught promise rejections in route handlers
- Secrets in code or committed .env files
